1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,600
I saw Auntie kill your mom.

2
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:28,120
Didn't you go pick up Aunt Pen?
Where's Aunt Pen?

3
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:30,160
Damn it!

4
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,760
Krongsuk, either you or I have to die.

5
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:35,280
<i>You want to see me</i>
<i>become a monster so badly? Fine.</i>

6
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:38,760
I also want to know if you still want me.

7
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,200
I'll let you have her, Mr. Tong.

8
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,920
Auntie! What are you going to do to Pin?

9
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,760
She saved me, Auntie!

10
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:08,040
How's it going, gorgeous?

11
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:09,840
Did you miss me?

12
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:13,800
Mr. Tong.

13
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:16,520
Madam didn't believe me?

14
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:20,360
Pan locked me and Ms. Nee up, really.

15
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:22,960
That's why I couldn't let anyone know.

16
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:25,320
We don't care who locked you up.

17
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,120
We just want to make sure

18
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:31,440
if Yai is really dead or not.

19
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:37,960
If he wasn't dead,
why would Pan torture me and Ms. Nee?

20
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:45,240
I didn't see it with my own eyes,

21
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:47,640
so you could be making things up.

22
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,400
Guys.

23
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,760
Mr. Tong, what are you doing?

24
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:04,640
Yai loves you so much.

25
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:08,120
If he finds out that the woman he loves

26
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,960
is about to die by suffocation,

27
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,360
he'll definitely show up.

28
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,760
Mr. Yai really is dead.

29
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,079
Mr. Yai is dead.

30
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,400
Mr. Yai is dead.

31
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,600
- This way, Mr. Na. Straight ahead.
- Yeah.

32
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:40,880
Well? Where's Yai?

33
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:42,880
Mr. Yai…

34
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,240
Mr. Yai really is dead.

35
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:49,560
Damn it. Where is he?

36
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:51,040
Tell me.

37
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,640
He's dead.

38
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:59,480
Hey. All of you.

39
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Stop right now.

40
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:04,920
You dare raise your voice at me?

41
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,600
You weakling. Go put on a skirt, will you?

42
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,280
Pin. Pin.

43
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:27,880
If you kill Pin, I'll fight you to death.

44
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,560
You love each other that much, huh?

45
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,200
Then die together.

46
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,760
That's enough.

47
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:43,400
If he crosses the line with you,
I'll deal with him myself.

48
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,920
Na, get out of here.

49
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:52,880
Go. Pin will be okay.

50
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,640
Go!

51
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,200
Could Yai really be dead?

52
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:35,960
Hey.

53
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,800
Auntie. Pin is okay, right?

54
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:41,920
I've warned you, haven't I?

55
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,560
Don't pick a fight with him over one girl.

56
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:46,320
You're throwing your life away for her.

57
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:47,880
Why are you so stupid?

58
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,560
I couldn't just stand by
and watch Pin die.

59
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:54,160
I love her, Auntie.

60
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,240
Keep it down.

61
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:59,520
You want Onsa-ang to tear you to pieces?

62
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:03,000
You forced me to be with her.

63
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:07,240
Do you even realize
how miserable I've been?

64
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:10,880
I've been so bitter

65
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,560
that I've lost the will
to face another day.

66
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,600
Why would you say that?

67
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:19,120
Everything I've done
has been to get the farm for you.

68
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,720
I don't want these assets anymore.

69
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,720
I want my happiness back.

70
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,160
I want to be with someone I love.

71
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:32,560
You mean…

72
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:38,120
I want to marry Pin.

73
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,400
Pin?

74
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:21,120
Noi told me you miraculously survived.

75
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,120
Aunt Un's spirit must have saved you.

76
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,640
I'm so glad.

77
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,640
Jom.

78
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:30,280
How did you get here?

79
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:34,520
Madam let me come back
to work for the farm.

80
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:36,919
She also made me supervisor
over all the workers.

81
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:40,000
Pin!

82
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:42,240
Pin!

83
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:45,480
Madam is allowing you to stay here now.

84
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:55,280
How could I possibly marry Mr. Na?

85
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:57,600
He already has Ms. On.

86
00:08:57,680 --> 00:09:00,360
I don't want to be a homewrecker.

87
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,440
It's a sin.

88
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:04,720
It's not that strange
for a man to have two wives.

89
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:07,720
Onsa-ang came first, so it's only right
to let her be the legitimate wife.

90
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,360
And for a maid like you,

91
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:12,640
becoming his mistress is fortunate enough.

92
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,200
What if I refuse to marry him?

93
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,760
Then you must leave the farm.

94
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,920
I have no room for ingrates on this farm.

95
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:23,040
Wait, Madam.

96
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,080
What if I agree to marry him?

97
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:32,800
What's in it for me?

98
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:37,840
I was right about you.

99
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:41,600
Deep down, you're evil and greedy.

100
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:46,640
I've been learning from you.

101
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,560
Once I sell the farm,

102
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:55,080
I'll give you half the money.

103
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,040
Agreed.

104
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:01,320
But I won't marry until the 100-day
mourning period for Mom is over.

105
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,760
I believe you can wait.

106
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,640
Pin agreed?

107
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,800
I love you the most, Auntie.

108
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:38,480
Why don't you go and demand an explanation

109
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:40,040
from Mr. Na on how he could do this?

110
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:43,080
How could he marry Pin
when he already has you?

111
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:44,600
This is outrageous.

112
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:45,920
Can you just shut up?

113
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,040
I don't want to hear it.

114
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:52,120
Miss On, should we go back
to the Secretary?

115
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:55,400
Why would you tolerate
being around these uncivilized people?

116
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:57,120
It's no use.

117
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:59,120
Who said it's no use?

118
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:02,680
No one walks all over me
and gets away with it.

119
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:54,960
Who are you?

120
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:57,120
Help! Help!

121
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:59,040
Pin. Hey, hey. It's me.

122
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,120
Mr. Yai?

123
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:12,800
Why did you come here? It's dangerous.

124
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:15,520
It's because it's dangerous
that I had to come.

125
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,800
Keep this knife for self-defense.

126
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:20,360
Remember, always keep it with you.

127
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:23,920
We agreed you wouldn't come here.

128
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,400
If we get caught, the plan will be ruined.

129
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:30,360
Mr. Yai. You can't go now, Mr. Yai.

130
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:32,600
What's the point of all this killing?

131
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:33,840
Let go of me, Pin.

132
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:35,800
To fight monsters,
I must be even more evil.

133
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:37,680
Would it bring Aunt Pen back to life?

134
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,040
Would it free Uncle Pload from prison?

135
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:44,200
If violence is the only answer,
why do we even have brains?

136
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:47,520
Pin is right.

137
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:50,360
Revenge doesn't really need a gun.

138
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,800
Right now, we have two enemies,

139
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,600
Tong and Madam.

140
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:04,680
The witch pulls the strings,
while that pervert does the dirty work.

141
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,560
Correct.

142
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:09,760
We need to expose
the truth that Madam killed Un

143
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:12,640
and framed you,
so Pload can finally walk free.

144
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:15,680
I'll do it myself.

145
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,960
Not a chance. I won't let you.

146
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:21,080
I'm not asking for permission.

147
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:22,720
I've made my decision.

148
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:24,520
I'll go back to Paisal Farm.

149
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:26,720
How are you going to get back in, Pin?

150
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:29,440
If you go, they'll know I'm still alive.

151
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:33,080
Ms. Nee will convince Madam to trust me.

152
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:35,440
What if Nee feels sorry for her mom

153
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,320
and tells her everything?

154
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:38,720
You'll be in danger.

155
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:40,840
Piece of cake.

156
00:16:40,920 --> 00:16:43,280
Tatsanee doesn't need to know a thing.
Problem solved.

157
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,320
I don't care anymore.

158
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:48,120
I just want to kill her. Come here!

159
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:51,040
- Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.
- Yai, give me the gun.

160
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,880
- Come, Ms. Nee. Let's go now.
- Let go, Yai.

161
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,520
Pin. Pin.

162
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:56,480
- Yai.
- Mr. Yai, stop.

163
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,560
If killing someone solves anything,

164
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:01,960
I'll shoot your head off first.

165
00:17:04,280 --> 00:17:06,760
Chief. You didn't need
to be that dramatic.

166
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:09,640
If the gun had gone off,
Pin would have ended up being a widow.

167
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,040
It doesn't have any rounds in it.

168
00:17:12,119 --> 00:17:13,760
Why? Did I scare you?

169
00:17:13,839 --> 00:17:15,640
Chief, Calm down.

170
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:17,760
Hey, what are you two playing at?

171
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,960
I was pretending to try to kill Tatsanee

172
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:23,000
to let Pin help her
run back to Paisal Farm.

173
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:25,680
Back to the farm? Why?

174
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:29,040
To find evidence to put Madam in prison.

175
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,840
I shouldn't have let you come.

176
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,400
You almost died because of me.

177
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:39,520
But I survived,
and I'm here right in front of you.

178
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,240
Pin.

179
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,040
Is something wrong?

180
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:00,200
Pin.

181
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:03,680
Pin. What's wrong?

182
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:05,480
- Open the door for me.
- Be safe.

183
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:07,680
I'll always keep an eye on you.

184
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:10,360
Always?

185
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:21,600
Pin.

186
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:29,240
I was patrolling this area

187
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,920
and heard people talking.

188
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:37,400
I dreamt about Mom, Jom.

189
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:40,960
I must have been sleeptalking.

190
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:44,480
I miss Mom.

191
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,880
I should go sleep in her room.

192
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,520
Go get some rest, Jom.

193
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:51,960
Don't worry about me.

194
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:23,120
Hey, Mr. Yai has been in there
for a while now.

195
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,680
He still hasn't come out of Pin's room.

196
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:29,960
Could they be "keeping each other warm"?

197
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:32,600
Hey, what was that? That's obscene.

198
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:34,000
What?

199
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:35,880
You're acting like we haven't done it.

200
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:37,920
We don't only keep warm.

201
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:38,960
We make each other hot.

202
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:41,160
- That's gross.
- You started it.

203
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:43,840
Come on. Oh. Mr. Yai.

204
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:44,920
You should hurry back.

205
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,440
Thank you for looking out for me.

206
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:49,760
Yes. Mr. Yai,

207
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:53,120
when Pin told us you're alive,
I was so glad.

208
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,880
Tell us any time you need help.

209
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:58,560
Waan and I will always be by your side.

210
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:01,680
Then, be careful.

211
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:02,680
Yes.

212
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,240
Let's go. Come on.

213
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:11,520
Mr. Yai?!

214
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:15,760
‪A ghost!

215
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:18,720
‪A ghost!

216
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:23,360
- A ghost…
- Don't scream. That's a man, not a ghost.

217
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:25,800
Mr. Yai's still alive.

218
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:28,920
Mr. Yai is alive?

219
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:30,360
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

220
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:32,360
- Hey, what's this?
- Are you still alive?

221
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,040
- Yeah.
- Why are you illuminating your face?

222
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:38,080
The Permanent Secretary
has promised to help?

223
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,440
That's great.

224
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:41,000
When should I pay him a visit?

225
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:43,280
He will be the one making an appointment.

226
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:47,520
It took me a long time to convince him.

227
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:50,600
I assured him that you've been

228
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:52,240
an excellent and impeccable host.

229
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,480
If I win the election,

230
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:01,160
he will be generously compensated
for his support.

231
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,640
He won't take any.

232
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:06,520
He'd let me have it instead.

233
00:21:10,760 --> 00:21:12,560
So, do you have

234
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:14,920
any figure in your mind?

235
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:18,800
I don't want money.

236
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:23,440
But I want to end someone's life.

237
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,200
You want me to kill someone?

238
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:42,760
I did what you told me to do, Dad.

239
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:44,800
Yai won't turn himself in,

240
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:47,640
but he'll help gather evidence
to bring Madam to justice.

241
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:49,960
How will you all find evidence

242
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:52,560
when you're not in Paisal Farm?

243
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,360
Well,

244
00:21:56,880 --> 00:22:00,400
we planted some of our team
inside the farm, just like in the movies.

245
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:03,320
So we won't need gunfights
like you had in your days.

246
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:04,960
Listen, Pan.

247
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,640
Don't even try joking with me.

248
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:12,840
Hey, how's Mr. Yai right now?

249
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:14,840
Has he lost or gained weight?

250
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:16,440
Is his appetite back to normal?

251
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:18,600
Why aren't you

252
00:22:19,520 --> 00:22:21,160
asking about me at all?

253
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:25,520
I'm seeing you right here
with my eyes, Pan.

254
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:28,120
What more do I need to ask about you?

255
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:31,120
It can be about any other things.

256
00:22:31,760 --> 00:22:34,800
Oh, Pan, go tell Aunt Pen

257
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:37,880
to make me some khanom la.

258
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:39,920
I'm really craving it.

259
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,040
Good luck, Pan.

260
00:23:15,440 --> 00:23:16,640
Khanom la,

261
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:18,960
I can find him some.

262
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:25,400
But Aunt Pen…

263
00:23:27,760 --> 00:23:29,800
I can't bring her back for him.

264
00:23:36,960 --> 00:23:38,840
We still have to keep it a secret.

265
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:42,360
Any progress on Aunt Pen's murder?

266
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:47,520
The police concluded that

267
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:52,120
Aunt Pen was killed during a robbery.

268
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:57,200
So I played along like you told me to.

269
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,840
Once our plan succeeds,

270
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:09,400
I'll get back at them for everything.

271
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:11,520
I've already asked the officer

272
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:15,760
to keep it a secret from Dad.

273
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,000
But I'm scared, Yai.

274
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:23,760
I'm scared Dad will ask me again.

275
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:27,520
I'm losing my mind.

276
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:35,360
Pan.

277
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,240
Why are you crying?

278
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:40,680
You're a grown-up, not a kid anymore.

279
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,560
I feel bad for Dad, Yai.

280
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:50,520
For as long as I can remember,

281
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:55,880
Dad and Aunt Pen
have always been inseparable.

282
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:01,800
I miss Aunt Pen.

283
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:14,000
You…

284
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:17,080
Aunt Pen didn't want you to be a crybaby.

285
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:18,720
Don't you remember?

286
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:21,000
Don't let me see you
being this weak again.

287
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:25,840
You have to be strong like Aunt Pen,

288
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:30,600
because Uncle Pload has only you now.

289
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:58,040
Mom,

290
00:25:58,960 --> 00:26:00,920
please watch over and protect me.

291
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:13,760
Ms. Nee?

292
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:19,360
I want to ask forgiveness
from Aunt Un's spirit on behalf of Auntie.

293
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,360
Those who commit sins

294
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:31,200
will face the consequences.

295
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,520
We can't ask for forgiveness
on someone else's behalf.

296
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:37,600
I don't know how to stop her.

297
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:40,320
You even almost died yesterday
because of her.

298
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:43,680
I believe in goodness.

299
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:47,040
If you do good, if you do things right,

300
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:48,520
you'll survive.

301
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:51,800
What if Mr. Yai follows us
and tries to kill us again?

302
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:55,920
He wouldn't do anything like that.

303
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:01,080
I mean

304
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:04,280
I won't let him do anything to you.

305
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:06,040
Please don't worry.

306
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:32,680
Look at you.

307
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:36,080
You're switching sides to get close
to your new sister-in-law, Tatsanee?

308
00:27:43,320 --> 00:27:44,160
Pin.

309
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:52,440
Ms. On?

310
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:57,000
Don't worry. I'm not picking a fight.

311
00:27:57,080 --> 00:27:58,800
I just want to negotiate.

312
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:07,720
Ms. On, why do we need
to come all the way here to talk?

313
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:10,680
I want to buy Na back.

314
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:11,960
How much do you want?

315
00:28:13,520 --> 00:28:16,080
I've never tried to take Mr. Na from you.

316
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:19,480
I've never even seen you
as a rival either.

317
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:23,200
So don't you dare talk
about taking him from me.

318
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:26,600
You're just a desperate widow
preying on other people's men.

319
00:28:27,760 --> 00:28:29,360
I have something

320
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:32,400
that I can't tell you about yet.

321
00:28:32,480 --> 00:28:33,520
But…

322
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:36,200
please trust me.

323
00:28:36,280 --> 00:28:37,760
When the time comes,

324
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:40,360
I'll do anything
to get Mr. Na back together with you.

325
00:28:40,440 --> 00:28:41,880
I promise.

326
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:44,760
Stop pretending.

327
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:49,600
You're not even worthy
to live in this world.

328
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:53,000
So I decided correctly then.

329
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:12,280
I brought her here for you.

330
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:37,800
I did the right thing.

331
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:40,840
Pin deserves to die.

332
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:43,520
Miss On. Miss On.

333
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:46,680
The workers told me
you were out driving with Pin.

334
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,000
Is something wrong? I'm worried.

335
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:51,200
You don't need to worry.

336
00:29:52,880 --> 00:29:55,480
Pin won't be able
to do anything to me anymore.

337
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:58,360
What does that mean, Miss On?

338
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:01,880
If I turn up as a corpse on this farm,

339
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:04,000
Mr. Na wouldn't let it slide.

340
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:09,000
That wimp? He can't do anything.

341
00:30:09,080 --> 00:30:10,920
He couldn't even keep
his fiancée in check.

342
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:13,960
That's the reason
why you have to die like this.

343
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:16,520
Honestly,

344
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:18,640
I'm so torn to see you go.

345
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:21,600
But I have no choice.

346
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:26,040
Close your eyes.

347
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:27,920
It'll be quick.

348
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:29,280
You won't even feel the pain.

349
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:33,200
Get it done.

350
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:35,880
And find somewhere to bury her.

351
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:38,240
Don't leave any tracks.

352
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:39,760
Yes, Boss.

353
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:43,440
<i>Mom, please help me.</i>

354
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:44,960
Boss.

355
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:47,720
The former municipal
council member called.

356
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:48,960
He said it's an urgent matter.

357
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:56,880
Miss On. How could you be so thoughtless?

358
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:58,800
Even if you don't do it yourself,

359
00:30:58,880 --> 00:31:00,960
you'd still be branded a murderer.

360
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,520
If she actually took Na from me,

361
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:06,640
I'd have to end them both.

362
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:09,840
I'd be a murderer anyway.

363
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:13,200
Miss On. Why…

364
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:18,840
Why would you risk your future
for a worthless man like Mr. Na?

365
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:21,760
Because I love him.

366
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:26,960
You've never been in love.

367
00:31:28,120 --> 00:31:31,640
You've never had someone,
so you wouldn't understand.

368
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:33,760
But Miss On…

369
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:35,640
Don't say anything else.

370
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:38,240
Just shut up. Get in.

371
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:40,880
Get in.

372
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:49,480
Don't ever talk about this again.

373
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:53,160
On tricked me!

374
00:31:53,760 --> 00:31:55,520
Her father was kicked out a long time ago.

375
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:57,600
So that's why

376
00:31:57,680 --> 00:32:00,240
she didn't want me to go see him
and kept making excuses.

377
00:32:00,320 --> 00:32:01,640
What should we do, Boss?

378
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:03,160
We've spent millions forming our empire.

379
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:05,040
Go get On and bring her to me.

380
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:06,880
What about her?

381
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:09,000
What do I even get from killing Pin?

382
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:10,520
Let her go.

383
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:38,480
Come here! Get out of there.

384
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:40,920
- Hey, stop right now. Let go.
- Why are you taking me?

385
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:45,720
I almost killed Pin for free.

386
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:48,120
You've got a lot of nerve
using me like that.

387
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:49,200
Who's using you?

388
00:32:49,280 --> 00:32:51,960
That big-shot father of yours
got busted for bid rigging.

389
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:53,520
He was dismissed
from the Ministry years ago.

390
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:55,160
But you didn't tell me that.

391
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:59,360
But Madam is the one
who came up with that story to trick you.

392
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:02,520
If Miss On doesn't do as Madam wants,
she'd have to break up with Mr. Na.

393
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:04,880
Madam was the one
tricking you, not Miss On.

394
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:07,160
I'll definitely settle
a score with that bitch.

395
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:09,440
I've lost so much because of her family.

396
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:10,480
Go, take her.

397
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:12,160
- Come here. Go.
- Let go of her!

398
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,760
- Let go of Miss On.
- Stay out of this.

399
00:33:14,840 --> 00:33:16,920
Miss On. Miss On.

400
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:24,600
Miss On. Miss On!

401
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:27,320
Miss On. Miss On.

402
00:33:33,360 --> 00:33:34,200
Let me go.

403
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,080
- Hey!
- Let go!

404
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:38,560
Hey. Stay still.

405
00:33:39,240 --> 00:33:40,160
Do you want to die?

406
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:47,600
Jan?

407
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:49,760
Let her go. Let Miss On go.

408
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:51,240
Let Miss On go now.

409
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:52,560
What do we do, Boss?

410
00:33:52,640 --> 00:33:53,640
Just run her over.

411
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:05,320
Jan.

412
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:22,480
Jan?

413
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:26,880
Jan. Jan.

414
00:34:27,520 --> 00:34:28,360
Jan.

415
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:30,400
Pin…

416
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:33,239
Pin… Help…

417
00:34:34,120 --> 00:34:37,360
Help Miss On…

418
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:39,520
Jan.

419
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:46,639
Jan. Jan.

420
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:49,880
Jan.

421
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:51,480
Pin!

422
00:34:52,679 --> 00:34:55,360
I saw you going out with Ms. On,
so I was worried.

423
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:58,720
Hey! Jan!

424
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:00,040
Jan!

425
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:01,720
Pin, what do we do?

426
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:04,080
- Call an ambulance. Call an ambulance.
- Your phone.

427
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:06,280
- Give me your phone.
- Call an ambulance.

428
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:09,400
Call an ambulance. Hurry.

429
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:12,280
What? Mr. Tong took On?

430
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:13,480
Why?

431
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:14,720
Well,

432
00:35:14,800 --> 00:35:17,960
I heard that Ms. On lied to him
about her father.

433
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:20,640
He was furious
and took Ms. On with him in his van.

434
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:23,840
Then, Jan tried to block them,
and they ran her over.

435
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:27,760
Mr. Na, you have to go help Ms. On.

436
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:29,400
What do I do?

437
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:33,400
Auntie, we should call the police.

438
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:38,960
Na.

439
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:43,440
Don't you want to marry Pinanong?

440
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:46,360
Mr. Tong is now getting rid of On for us.

441
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:47,560
Isn't that convenient?

442
00:35:48,160 --> 00:35:51,640
But it's not like
I want On to die, Auntie.

443
00:35:51,720 --> 00:35:54,400
Live or die, it's up to her fate.
It has nothing to do with us.

444
00:35:54,920 --> 00:35:56,080
Trust me,

445
00:35:56,600 --> 00:35:59,000
and you'll get everything you want.

446
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:07,320
- Noi.
- Pin. Jan didn't make it, Pin.

447
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:09,960
Jan is gone.

448
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:13,920
The doctor said Jan passed away
on the way to the hospital.

449
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,400
What did you tell them
about her cause of death?

450
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:18,680
I said she got hit by a car.

451
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:22,640
The doctor told us to report it,
so I rushed back to tell you first.

452
00:36:23,240 --> 00:36:24,120
Good.

453
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:26,880
Don't let the police know about this

454
00:36:27,400 --> 00:36:29,080
because it happened on our farm.

455
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:30,760
I don't want chaos here.

456
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:32,760
And about the body,

457
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:35,040
just leave it at the hospital for now.

458
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:37,360
A person has died, Madam.

459
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:39,120
It's not like just a dog got run over.

460
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:41,240
How could we leave her there?

461
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:43,600
Mr. Tong killed her.

462
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:46,520
Do you want him to take us out too?

463
00:36:48,480 --> 00:36:50,760
And what should we do
about Ms. On being kidnapped?

464
00:36:55,040 --> 00:36:56,240
All of you.

465
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:59,080
Remember what I'm about to say.

466
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:02,040
On was upset with Na.

467
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:04,280
She broke up with Na

468
00:37:05,120 --> 00:37:08,360
and announced
that she would leave this farm.

469
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:12,440
After that, no one knew anything else,
and no one saw her.

470
00:37:12,520 --> 00:37:13,360
Do you understand?

471
00:37:14,640 --> 00:37:15,800
Do you understand?

472
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:29,080
<i>The number you have called</i>
<i>is not available at the moment.</i>

473
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:33,000
Mr. Yai. When something fatal happens,
you decide to turn off your phone?

474
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:43,760
Your blood pressure pills, dear.

475
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:07,760
On hasn't called you at all?

476
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:12,440
She has, but I saw

477
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:15,400
that you were asleep,
so I didn't want to wake you up.

478
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:18,280
On is so worried about you.

479
00:38:18,360 --> 00:38:22,040
She insisted you take all your medicine.

480
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:24,960
Don't lie to me.

481
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:27,800
In her eyes,

482
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:32,800
I'm nothing but a useless old fool.

483
00:38:37,480 --> 00:38:39,680
She might not even consider me
her father anymore.

484
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:48,240
On, how have you been?

485
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:50,160
Your father just asked about you.

486
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:52,280
Who is that?

487
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:55,200
Lady, if you want
your daughter back alive,

488
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:58,680
bring me 10 million by today.

489
00:39:00,920 --> 00:39:02,160
Here. Talk to her yourself.

490
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:05,360
Mom. Don't come here, Mom.

491
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:07,840
Mom.

492
00:39:07,920 --> 00:39:10,080
I'll send you the location.

493
00:39:10,600 --> 00:39:12,360
If you tell the police,

494
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,680
<i>you'll get your daughter back as a corpse.</i>

495
00:39:18,080 --> 00:39:21,200
This is the price for tricking me.

496
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:28,760
Wait here.

497
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:31,240
By midnight,

498
00:39:31,760 --> 00:39:34,880
that lady will come
to exchange the money for her.

499
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:37,000
Count it and make sure it's right.

500
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:40,280
After that,
silence both the mother and the daughter.

501
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:47,240
Didn't you say you'd let me go
once you had the money?

502
00:39:47,320 --> 00:39:49,280
Huh? You liar!

503
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:51,080
You bastard! You scum!

504
00:39:51,160 --> 00:39:55,080
- You bastard!
- Go on, curse me all you want.

505
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:57,280
You won't get to speak for much longer.

506
00:39:58,640 --> 00:39:59,720
Keep a close eye on her.

507
00:40:17,480 --> 00:40:18,440
Hello.

508
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:20,840
Na, it's me.

509
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:23,520
Did you know On was kidnapped?

510
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:25,360
<i>They demanded a ransom of 10 million baht.</i>

511
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:26,840
I…

512
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:31,440
I don't know about that. Well…

513
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:33,920
On came to me earlier.

514
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:35,880
We had a fight,

515
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:38,880
and then she left the farm.

516
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:43,280
The captors told me
to give them the money near Paisal Farm.

517
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:44,600
I've got the money.

518
00:40:44,680 --> 00:40:46,880
But can you go with me?

519
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:50,120
I'm waiting at the farm entrance.

520
00:40:52,720 --> 00:40:54,920
I told you not to get involved with them.

521
00:40:56,040 --> 00:40:56,960
Hello.

522
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:58,560
I'm so sorry.

523
00:40:58,640 --> 00:41:00,800
I can't let my son risk his life for this,

524
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:03,720
since we no longer have
anything to do with each other.

525
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:06,120
Auntie.

526
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:09,800
Well, On's mother is on her way
to pay her ransom.

527
00:41:10,640 --> 00:41:12,400
I want to keep her company.

528
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:15,880
Didn't you say they're bankrupt?

529
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:18,400
So this means they've been lying to us.

530
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:21,160
Then it's only right
to let them face the music.

531
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:26,000
Or if you want to die horribly like Jan,

532
00:41:26,080 --> 00:41:27,840
go ahead, go with that lady.

533
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:39,520
Wait, ma'am.

534
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:43,800
Who are you?

535
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:48,560
My name is Pin. I work here at the farm.

536
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:50,800
You're going to save Ms. On, aren't you?

537
00:41:51,520 --> 00:41:53,000
You knew about this too?

538
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:56,360
I know the way around here.

539
00:41:56,440 --> 00:41:58,080
I'll go with you.

540
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:06,240
I brought the money.

541
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:10,040
On.

542
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:11,600
Mom…

543
00:42:15,040 --> 00:42:16,240
Let Ms. On go.

544
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:20,640
Untie me. Let me go.

545
00:42:20,720 --> 00:42:21,760
Let me go!

546
00:42:24,480 --> 00:42:27,640
- Mom!
- On. Are you okay, dear?

547
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:31,240
Are you hurt anywhere? Are you okay?

548
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:32,600
Are you alright?

549
00:42:35,480 --> 00:42:37,600
Where did you get the money from?

550
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:39,560
We didn't have money anymore, did we?

551
00:42:39,640 --> 00:42:41,600
I took the last piece of garden land

552
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:46,240
Grandma left me and pleaded
with a respected elder to mortgage it.

553
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:48,920
Mom…

554
00:43:01,840 --> 00:43:02,960
‪Hey.

555
00:43:08,560 --> 00:43:10,160
You've already got the money.

556
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:11,520
What else do you want?

557
00:43:11,600 --> 00:43:13,760
Both your lives!

558
00:43:15,360 --> 00:43:18,120
Let them go and take me instead.

559
00:43:20,160 --> 00:43:21,960
You'll get a double win this way.

560
00:43:22,040 --> 00:43:23,680
I'm Mr. Yai's wife.

561
00:43:23,760 --> 00:43:25,840
My price is Paisal Farm.

562
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:29,840
Don't listen to her. Kill them!

563
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:43,200
Run.

564
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:06,480
Take them alive.

565
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:07,880
We need them as witnesses.

566
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:26,200
Hey! Fall back!

567
00:44:46,760 --> 00:44:48,480
Hey. Yai!

568
00:44:49,680 --> 00:44:51,040
This bitch betrayed me.

569
00:44:51,120 --> 00:44:53,000
- Hey!
<i>- Come work for me.</i>

570
00:44:53,080 --> 00:44:55,720
And you'll be in charge
of all his businesses.

571
00:44:55,800 --> 00:44:57,120
<i>Why do you still love him?</i>

572
00:44:57,200 --> 00:44:59,720
Tell me. Why, Pin? Pin!

573
00:45:01,160 --> 00:45:02,000
Mr. Na.

574
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:11,640
- Dad?
- I saw his face.

575
00:45:11,720 --> 00:45:13,080
Who is "he"?

576
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:56,240
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
